    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay so i get that they work together. but i was thinking about the actual bond between them. since the steel is literally buried inside the solid concrete, how does the concrete actually \"grip\" the rebar so they don't just slide past each other when the load hits? is it just friction or is there something else happening deep inside the concrete that holds it all together?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
